 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-SPEC-003: Implement FP/FN calibration loop for harvest quality self-improvement. PROBLEM: harvest.rs HarvestQuality tracks count but no FP/FN rates. No mechanism detects whether committed candidates were later retracted (FP) or rejected candidates were re-discovered (FN). No threshold adjustment logic. INV-HARVEST-004 specifies calibration: high FP → raise threshold, high FN → lower threshold. SOLUTION: (1) After harvest, query for retracted harvest entities (FP indicator). (2) Query for observations matching previously-rejected candidates (FN indicator). (3) Adjust confidence threshold via calibration: new_threshold = old_threshold + learning_rate * (FP_rate - target_FP). (4) Store calibration results as datoms. VERIFICATION: (1) proptest: after N harvests with known FP/FN, threshold converges to optimal. (2) Unit test: high FP rate increases threshold. DEPENDS-ON: W2-006 (crystallization guard provides the threshold to calibrate). INTERACTS-WITH: W0-005 (retraction detection needed for FP measurement)."
